The article states that the United States government has assessed with high confidence that the Syrian government carried out a chemical weapons attack in the Damascus suburbs on August 21, 2013. They further assess that the regime used a nerve agent in the attack. This assessment is based on various sources of intelligence, including human, signals, and geospatial intelligence, as well as open source reporting. The article also mentions that the Syrian regime has a stockpile of chemical agents and munitions that can be used for chemical warfare. The regime has been assessed to have used chemical weapons on a small scale against the opposition multiple times in the past year. The article provides details on the preparations for the attack, the attack itself, and the aftermath, including the symptoms observed in victims and the response of the international community. The US government concludes that there is a substantial body of information that implicates the Syrian government's responsibility for the chemical weapons attack.